      "name": "Material property literature synthesis for Ti-6Al-4V pedicle screw",
      "description": "A comprehensive synthesis of multiple prior studies characterizing the elastic modulus, yield strength, and fatigue behavior of medical-grade Ti-6Al-4V implant alloy. This synthesis consolidates findings from cadaveric biomechanical studies, ISO 5832-3 coupon testing programs, and prior FDA submissions, providing the material property inputs used in the FEA model ensemble. The breadth of source material and the consistency of reported values across independent laboratories lend high confidence to the parameter set adopted here. Cross-laboratory agreement (CV < 4% on elastic modulus) further supports the robustness of the synthesis.",
